Kwaito king Arthur Mafokate has allegedly stolen R6m from his South Africa Arts and Development Association (Saada) nonprofit organisation (NPO) and used it to buy himself a guesthouse in Midrand, Joburg. The R6m was left over from the R9.5m the organisation received from the National Lottery Commission (NLC) in 2014 to unearth and develop talent across the country. TO READ MORE ON THIS STORY GET A COPY OF TODAY'S SUNDAY WORLD 